narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Writing skills, knowledge on my topic.
How to research in primary sources and secondary literature for a history senior essay. How to write an annotate bibliography and first ten pages of senior essay.
I did a ton of great research, and learned that I'm basically on my own with that research. No one cares what I'm doing, and it's all up to me.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Would love to have a mid-semester info session like there is for on-cycle students. Ended up learning about deadlines through a friend often and didn't realize there was a canvas page until mid-semester

If you haven't been working on developing relationships with professors throughout your time at Yale, you're in a bad place. And no one teaches you how to do that. I felt incredibly on my own with this.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Required for history major so yes!
What's the point of this? You have to do it. Try to get the most out of it and produce worthwhile scholarship.
